11. ONBOARDING & TRUST
The onboarding flow is one of the most critical systems in the entire product.
It must:

Build trust

Reduce fear

Explain safety

Show value instantly

Minimize friction

Deliver an emotional “first win”

Convert users into daily cleaners

This page defines the full onboarding system, including:

Safety messaging

Permission explanations

First‑time experience

Emotional reassurance

Quick‑start flow

Trust‑building UI patterns

Copywriting principles

Behavioral psychology

11.1 Onboarding Philosophy
1. Trust before access
Users must feel safe before connecting their inbox.

2. Emotion before logic
We reduce anxiety first, then explain features.

3. Transparency always
No hidden behavior.
No surprises.
No auto‑actions.

4. First win fast
Users must swipe their first email within 30 seconds of signup.

5. Safety as a feature
Undo everywhere.
Metadata‑only AI.
No content reading.

6. Zero cognitive load
Short sentences.
Simple visuals.
One decision per screen.

11.2 Onboarding Flow Overview
The onboarding flow has 7 stages:

Welcome Screen

The Problem

The Promise

Safety & Trust

Connect Inbox

Tutorial Swipe

First Real Cleanup

Each stage is detailed below.

11.3 Stage 1 — Welcome Screen
Purpose
Set tone

Establish brand personality

Create emotional resonance

UI
Clean hero illustration

“Swipe your inbox clean in seconds.”

CTA: “Get Started”

Psychology
Reduce friction

Create curiosity

Establish simplicity

11.4 Stage 2 — The Problem
Purpose
Make users feel understood.

Copy Examples
“Your inbox is overflowing.”

“Newsletters, promos, spam — it never stops.”

“Cleaning it manually takes hours.”

Visuals
Animated inbox filling up

Red notification bubbles

Psychology
Empathy

Shared frustration

Emotional alignment

11.5 Stage 3 — The Promise
Purpose
Show the transformation.

Copy Examples
“Clean your inbox with simple swipes.”

“Delete, unsubscribe, block — instantly.”

“Feel lighter in seconds.”

Visuals
Swipe animation

Clean inbox reveal

Psychology
Relief

Hope

Motivation

11.6 Stage 4 — Safety & Trust
This is the most important onboarding step.

Purpose
Remove fear and build trust.

Key Messages
We never read your email content.

AI uses metadata only.

Undo everywhere — nothing is permanent.

No auto‑actions — you’re always in control.

You can disconnect anytime.

UI
Shield icon

Simple bullet points

“Learn more” expandable section

Psychology
Reduce anxiety

Increase confidence

Build credibility

11.7 Stage 5 — Connect Inbox
Purpose
Get access to email provider.

Providers
Gmail

Outlook

Yahoo

iCloud

Fastmail

IMAP

UI
Provider buttons

OAuth screens

“We never store your password” message

Friction Reduction
Show provider logos

Show trust badges

Show privacy reassurance

Psychology
Familiarity

Safety

Ease

11.8 Stage 6 — Tutorial Swipe
The user must experience the core mechanic immediately.

Tutorial Steps
Show a fake email card

Highlight swipe directions

Ask user to swipe right (unsubscribe)

Show animation + sound

Show “Nice!” message

Ask user to swipe left (delete)

Show combo animation

Tutorial Goals
Teach swipe directions

Build confidence

Deliver dopamine

Remove fear

Psychology
Mastery

Competence

Momentum

11.9 Stage 7 — First Real Cleanup
Purpose
Deliver the first real emotional win.

Flow
Load 10 real emails

User swipes through them

Show progress bar

Trigger combo

Trigger mini victory screen

Victory Screen
“You cleared 10 emails!”

“Time saved: 1.2 minutes”

“You’re off to a great start.”

Psychology
Achievement

Relief

Motivation to continue

11.10 Trust‑Building UI Patterns
1. Transparency Panels
Show exactly what the app can and cannot do.

2. Safety Badges
“Undo everywhere”

“Metadata‑only AI”

“No auto‑actions”

3. Provider Logos
Increases trust.

4. Micro‑copy
Short, reassuring messages.

5. No dark patterns
No forced actions.
No hidden settings.

11.11 Copywriting Principles
Tone
Calm

Friendly

Confident

Reassuring

Rules
Short sentences

No jargon

No fear‑based language

No guilt

No pressure

Examples
“You’re always in control.”

“Nothing is permanent.”

“Undo is always available.”

“We never read your email content.”

11.12 Behavioral Psychology Principles
1. Reduce Uncertainty
Clear explanations reduce anxiety.

2. Provide Safety Nets
Undo reduces fear of mistakes.

3. Show Immediate Progress
First win builds momentum.

4. Build Identity
“You’re someone who keeps your inbox clean.”

5. Avoid Shame
No “inbox zero” guilt.

11.13 Onboarding Success Metrics
Time to first swipe (< 30 seconds)

Inbox connection rate

Tutorial completion rate

First session completion rate

Day‑1 retention

Day‑7 retention
